Grinding money basically just means to run boring free/cheap kits, speedrun looting the map until you have 5m and can play normally again. snippet.textDisplay: I find myself in a challenging situation. I am interested in participating in the expedition; however, I started the game late and currently have only about 50 hours of playtime. While I would like to engage in the expedition for the sake of "bragging rights," I believe that the buffs should be permanent rather than temporary to provide a greater advantage for casual players. As a full-time working father with family commitments, I cannot dedicate as much time as I would like, yet I still find the game enjoyable and wish to be part of this experience. At this point, I may only earn one skill point, which benefits those who can invest significant time in the game. For casual players like myself, the rewards seem limited to 12 extra inventory slots, potentially one skill point, and temporary buffs that I may not fully utilize. With the holiday season upon us and family visiting, along with my work obligations, I am still contemplating my participation. I genuinely enjoy the game and recognize that participation is not mandatory; this is simply a consideration I wanted to share.
